<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1325,1323,1870]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,378,1323,1349]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was established by Bezzi (
<number box="[867,927,1324,1350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1921.0">1921</number>
a) in his key and diagnosis based on specimens from O’okiep and Knysna in 
<collectionCode box="[805,892,1364,1390]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SAMC</collectionCode>
. However, he does not provide the numbers of specimens or their sexes believing that the 
<typeStatus box="[950,1001,1404,1430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
specimen was in 
<collectionCode box="[1227,1319,1404,1430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">BMNH</collectionCode>
. Unfortunately, this 
<typeStatus box="[491,542,1444,1470]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
was not published until 
<number box="[830,889,1444,1470]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1924.0">1924</number>
and based on different material. The specimens in 
<collectionCode box="[428,511,1484,1510]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SAMC</collectionCode>
mentioned in his 
<number box="[731,790,1484,1510]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1921.0">1921</number>
publication are 
<typeStatus box="[987,1093,1484,1510]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Hesse (
<number box="[1195,1256,1484,1510]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1938.0">1938</number>
) provided a full redescription (as 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" box="[621,886,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis box="[621,886,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amictogeron barbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with figures of the genitalia of the single male from O’okiep. He also described a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" box="[1030,1315,1564,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis box="[1030,1315,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amictogeron peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on two males from Knysna, which were the specimens referred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" box="[1068,1207,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1207,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">G. barbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Bezzi (
<number box="[273,335,1644,1670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1921.0">1921</number>
a). Since 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" box="[449,600,1644,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,600,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amictogeron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hesse has been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[1033,1207,1644,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1107,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Geron</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
in which Hesse also proposed a species, 
<taxonomicName box="[646,857,1684,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis box="[646,857,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Geron peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hesse, the species described in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amictogeron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was renamed 
<taxonomicName authority="Bowden (1974)" authorityName="Bowden" authorityYear="1974" box="[525,875,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hessei">
<emphasis box="[525,679,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Geron hessei</emphasis>
Bowden (
<number box="[802,866,1724,1750]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1974.0">1974</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The listing of an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus box="[298,400,1764,1790]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">syntypes</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[442,525,1764,1790]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SAMC</collectionCode>
by Evenhuis &amp; Greathead (
<number box="[864,925,1764,1790]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1999.0">1999</number>
) requires amending to three 
<typeStatus pageId="15" pageNumber="16">syntypes</typeStatus>
[here = 
<typeStatus box="[424,531,1804,1830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<number box="[589,604,1804,1830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
<typeStatus box="[611,784,1804,1830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
] in 
<collectionCode box="[827,914,1804,1830]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SAMC</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1325,1323,1870]" lastBlockId="16.[264,1322,284,630]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The 
<typeStatus box="[367,470,1844,1870]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">syntypes</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[511,601,1844,1870]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">MSNM</collectionCode>
are not mentioned in any of Bezzi’s publications. However, the male from Knysna bears the same date as the two males in 
<collectionCode box="[1000,1083,284,310]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">SAMC</collectionCode>
and must have been part of the same series and its status is confirmed. The genitalia are exposed and can be seen to be those of 
<emphasis box="[496,662,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[496,659,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">G. peringueyi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which Hesse (
<number box="[839,900,364,390]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1938.0">1938</number>
) described from the two specimens from Knysna in 
<collectionCode box="[463,550,404,430]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">SAMC</collectionCode>
. The female from Caledon cannot be allocated with certainty to either 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1938" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1938" box="[340,478,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis box="[340,478,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">G. barbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[522,688,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[522,684,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">G. peringueyi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as there are no associated male specimens. Since no specimens from Caledon are mentioned in Bezzi’s publications, the status of the female as a 
<typeStatus box="[284,375,524,550]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">syntype</typeStatus>
cannot be confirmed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1322,284,630]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
For stability in the nomenclature the male specimen from O’okiep in 
<collectionCode box="[1182,1265,564,590]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">SAMC</collectionCode>
that Hesse (
<number box="[350,411,604,630]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1938.0">1938</number>
) described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezzi" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1938" box="[578,808,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Amictogeron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis box="[578,715,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. barbatus</emphasis>
(Bezzi)
</taxonomicName>
is designated 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[975,1087,603,629]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<typeStatus box="[975,1087,603,629]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lectotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
